   "source": [
    "# CO₂ Solubility in Water\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how to calculate the solubility of CO₂ in water using the NeqSim library. NeqSim is a library for thermodynamic and fluid property calculations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Setup and Installation\n",
    "\n",
    "First, ensure that you have Java installed on your system. Then, install the NeqSim library using pip."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install neqsim"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## CO₂ Solubility Calculation\n",
    "\n",
    "After installing NeqSim, we'll define the system and calculate the solubility of CO₂ in water at a given temperature and pressure."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from neqsim.thermo import fluid, TPflash\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define the temperature (in Kelvin) and pressure (in bar)\n",
    "temperature = 298.15  # 25°C\n",
    "pressure = 10.0       # 10 bar\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create a fluid system with water and CO2\n",
    "fluid_system = fluid('srk')\n",
    "fluid_system.addComponent('water', 1.0)  # 1 mol of water\n",
    "fluid_system.addComponent('CO2', 1.0)    # 1 mol of CO2\n",
    "fluid_system.setMultiPhaseCheck(True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set temperature and pressure\n",
    "fluid_system.setTemperature(temperature)\n",
    "fluid_system.setPressure(pressure)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Perform a thermodynamic flash calculation\n",
    "TPflash(fluid_system)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get the solubility of CO2 in water (mole fraction)\n",
    "co2_in_water = fluid_system.getPhase(1).getComponent('CO2').getx()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display results\n",
    "print(f'At {temperature} K and {pressure} bar:')\n",
    "print(f'The mole fraction of CO2 dissolved in water is approximately {co2_in_water:.6f}.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Interactive Exploration (Optional)\n",
    "\n",
    "You can use sliders to interactively change temperature and pressure."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from ipywidgets import interact\n",
    "\n",
    "def calculate_co2_solubility(temperature, pressure):\n",
    "    fluid_system.setTemperature(temperature)\n",
    "    fluid_system.setPressure(pressure)\n",
    "    TPflash(fluid_system)\n",
    "    co2_in_water = fluid_system.getPhase(1).getComponent('CO2').getx()\n",
    "    print(f'At {temperature} K and {pressure} bar:')\n",
    "    print(f'The mole fraction of CO2 dissolved in water is approximately {co2_in_water:.6f}.')\n",
    "\n",
    "interact(calculate_co2_solubility, \n",
    "         temperature=(273.15, 373.15, 1.0), \n",
    "         pressure=(1.0, 100.0, 1.0))"
   ]
  },
